{
  "texts": [
    "Figure 17 shows an example with two attention heads.",
    "The first head \"Head 1\" focused on the co-relevance between it and dog whereas the second head \"Head 2\" focused on the co-relevance between sat and tired.",
    "In this example, the concatenation matrix learned to combine the co-relevancies from both heads into single representation combining them.",
    "The GPT-3 implementation of attention heads maps the Q-K-V representation vectors to a lower dimension so that the computational cost for the combined heads would be equivalent to that for a single head of the full dimension.",
    "GPT-3 reduced the dimension of each head from 12,288 to 12,288/96 = 128."
  ]
}